President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation recognizing April 2, 2020, as World Autism Awareness Day. The proclamation acknowledges the millions of Americans living with autism spectrum disorder (ASD) and their triumphs over various obstacles. The President expresses gratitude to those who support individuals with ASD and emphasizes his commitment to ensuring their prosperity. The proclamation highlights legislation that provides funding for research, treatments, and support services for individuals with ASD. It also mentions efforts to improve early detection and treatment, enhance healthcare provider expertise, and promote the successful transition of individuals with ASD into rewarding careers and independent living. The President calls upon all Americans to learn about autism, understand the challenges faced by individuals with ASD, and find ways to support them and their families.